5475146.title: This Week's GSS Sessions
5475146.message: Hey everyone, I'll be holding two GSS Sessions this week on T/Th from 4pm - 4:50pm in MTH0103. We'll be covering the Cross Product, Lines, and Planes on Tuesday and Section 12.1 (Definitions/Intro to Vector Valued Functions) on Thursday. Also, if you plan to attend either session this week, we ask that you pre-register for them at this link . This link is to MyWCOnline, the website GSS uses to track our attendance. An account with your ELMS login credentials should already be created for you to log in to. If you have any issues registering for a session, please still attend. We can figure out the issue together at the session. I've also attached last week's Tuesday activity to this announcement for those who could not attend. 9-3 Activities.pdf

5463356.title: GSS Session Info
5463356.message: Hey everyone, Like I said on the first day, I’m Josh, your GSS Leader for this semester. I’ll be holding 2 50 minute sessions each week throughout the whole semester to review lecture topics and practice problems. The purpose of these sessions is to give you guys time to work through the concepts in a collaborative environment. We’ll do things like games, partners, board work, etc. I’m looking forward to this semester and if anyone has questions about the structure of GSS feel free to reach out, my email should be on ELMS. I’ve included the basic information about the sessions like time/place below: Times: T/Th 4pm-5pm (Sessions start Tuesday, 9/3) Place: MTH0103

5454134.title: Math 241 — no webassign
5454134.message: Dear class, I look forward to seeing you all tomorrow for our first class! In advance of that, I wanted to point out that in spite of what Testudo/the bookstore might have you believe, we are not using webassign for homeworks (we have no graded homeworks!). If you have purchased webassign, I suggest you see about returning it. Additionally, there are cheaper ways to get the textbook than via the bookstore (for example, getting the ebook via Cengage Unlimited). Jamie Conway
